         <div type="translation">
            <ab>MH 502, recto: (1) Pikos, son of Krour, has paid to the bank of (2) the norhtern houses for silver of poll of year 6 in Jeme, 2 staters (3) / 1 stater / 2 staters again. Written in year 6 of Tiberius, Pharmouthi 15. (4) Likewise, on Pachons 26, 2 staters / 1 stater / 2 staters again.</ab>
